Tensions are running high in Walmer township after the murder of a popular former teacher who ran a school homework club in the area. Unemployed Bathandwa Ndwanyana, 40, who started the Bona Bathandwa Dream Club to help primary and high school pupils in the township with their homework, was found dead in Topiya Street just before 10pm on Thursday. He had been shot. Residents said they knew who the shooter was, but were afraid to go to the police for fear of retribution. Ndwanyana was a good community leader . . . however, people are scared to come out about the murder, a resident, who did not want to be named, said. Another resident said: We are all sad about Ndwanyana s death as he has helped change the lives of the Walmer township kids. He taught them basic skills and also fed them daily. For the full story read The Herald, or get the complete newspaper, including comics, classifieds, crosswords and back editions in our e-Edition. &nbsp; Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share